Keansburg Steamboat Company, Libelant-Appellant, v. Steam Tug INVINCIBLE, Her Engines, etc.; Brooklyn Eastern District Terminal, Claimant-Appellee. Brooklyn Eastern District Terminal, Libelant- Appellee, v. Steamship SMITHFIELD, Her Engines, etc.; Keansburg Steamboat Company, Claimant-Appellant. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. May 17, 1926.) Nos. 381, 382. Alexander & Ash, of New York City (Peter Alexander, of New York City, of counsel), for the Smithfield. Bigham, Englar & Jones, of New York City (L. J. Matteson, of New York City, for the Invincible.

Before HOUGH, MANTON, and MACK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decrees (12 F.[2d] 959), affirmed, with costs.
